Tom is right that as part of any scheduleable HTTP (or other
recognizably hierarchical) URI, there will be a &#39;/&#39; after the
hostname portion, preventing a tail &#39;au&#39; match.

However, in order to fetch &#39;http://www.goldendragonpalace.com.au/&#39;,
the DNS lookup must first succeed, and this proceeds through the
normal crawling loop as URI &#39;dns:www.goldendragonpalace.com.au&#39;,
which would match the exclude filter.

The hint that this is happening is that -63 status code, a code
more recently added (split off from the previous -6 for all
prerequisite failures).

-63 is specifically S_PREREQUISITE_UNSCHEDULABLE_FAILURE, meaning
the given URI couldn&#39;t complete because its prequisite URI was
refused scheduling (ruled out of scope, even with the various
affordances usually granted prerequisites).

- Gordon @ IA

